Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_metric_alias(25.10)                                set_metric_alias(25.10)

Name
       set_metric_alias  -  Renames a metric name, prefixed with the name of a
       layer, analysis view, path group etc, to another name

Syntax
       set_metric_alias

       [-help]

       -from <old_name>

       [-no_overwrite]

       [-order <order_of_priority>]

       -to <new_name>

       Renames a metric name, prefixed with the  name  of  a  layer,  analysis
       view,  path  group  etc,  to  another name. For example, you can rename
       path_group:reg2reg to reg2reg using the set_metric_alias command.

Parameters
       -from <old_name>
              Specifies the metric object name to be changed.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each set_metric_alias parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man set_metric_alias.

       -no_overwrite
              Specifies to not overwrite an already set alias.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -order <order_of_priority>
              Specifies the order of priority of metric object in tables.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -to <new_name>
              Specifies the new name for the metric object.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
              *

                The  following  command  renames path_group:reg2reg to reg2reg
                with priority order 1.

                > set_metric_alias -from path_group:reg2reg -to reg2reg -order
                1

              *

                The  following   command   renames   path_group:reg2cgate   to
                reg2cgate with priority order 2.

                >  set_metric_alias  -from  path_group:reg2cgate -to reg2cgate
                -order 2

              *

                The following command queries the set of aliases:

                > get_metric_alias

                Output

                >path_group:reg2reg {to reg2reg order 1}  path_group:reg2cgate
                {to reg2cgate order 2}

